is this weird ever since i was younger i have enjoyed walking in cemeteries if i'm in a new city and see an older cemetery with old gravestones i stop and take a walk i like reading the headstones and imagining what kind of life the person had what they wore what they did for fun or work if they had a family etc sometimes i sit on a bench and just look around its so peaceful i'm not a crazy person or anything i'm not obsessed with death i have a normal life and family i have done this visit cemeteries since i was a child i'd ride my bike and look for the oldest headstone in the cemetery and imagine about the person's life i always go during daytime hours though because i find cemeteries creepy at night has anyone else ever done this am i just weird not weird at all i grew up in new england i stumbled across more than one hidden cemetary with old fascinating stones brings back memories yeah there's a certain serenity about cemetaries Headstone Squidward Tentacles Rosa Parks Jewish bereavement The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe Commonwealth War Graves Commission Oakland Cemetery 11:14 The Life and Times of Juniper Lee Arlington National Cemetery "Weird Al" Yankovic Charles Dickens John Lennon Milton H. Erickson Shaggy dog story The Amber Spyglass Elektra (comics) __douard Manet Whose Line Is It Anyway? Jackass: The Movie Arthur Machen Cemetery Invader Zim Elijah Wood Science fiction The SpongeBob SquarePants Movie Urinary incontinence Charmed Burial Lee Harvey Oswald Aerosmith Recumbent bicycle The Death Gate Cycle K' Doug Jon Secada Sleeping Murder Disneyland Pitaten Scenes from a Memory The Fairly OddParents Heinrich M__ller The Haunted Mansion Spidey Super Stories Avenue Q Datalore (TNG episode) Clark Ashton Smith H.P. Lovecraft Monty Python Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Edgar Allan Poe Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Funeral Comanche KaBlam! Glasnevin Cemetery John Peel Vertigo (film) John Berryman The Ashlee Simpson Show Captain Thunderbolt Serial killer The Inside